body_html:
This doesn't seem like it's necessarily a bug in the object detection code. I agree that the error message about Tensor shapes: "Expected [1,?,?,3], got [1,157,80,4]" suggests that the API is looking for RGB input data but something in your input data is somehow being decoded into depth-4, rather than depth-3.
You do say that you're using your own input data. Can you add checks about the cleanliness of your input dataset?

I think in many ways, this question is better asked on StackOverflow since it is not a bug or feature request. There is also a larger community that reads questions there. Thanks!
